<p>Val d'Orcia looks like a Renaissance painting because it <em>is</em> the Renaissance painting. Those rolling hills, lone cypress trees, and golden wheat fields you've seen in Tuscan wedding photos? That's this region, now a UNESCO World Heritage Site for its cultural landscape.</p>

<p><a href="/styles/villa">Villa</a> La Foce sits at the heart of it, a 15th-century estate famous for its formal Italian gardens designed by Cecil Pinsent. But here's what makes it special for weddings: the Grand Gallery. This indoor space can accommodate 220 seated guests, solving Tuscany's biggest practical problem—weather backup—without compromising elegance.</p>

<p>The estate includes multiple farmhouses that can accommodate 65 guests total, making it ideal for multi-day celebrations where everyone stays together, sharing meals at the villa and exploring Pienza and Montepulciano during downtime.</p>

<p class="mt-8 mb-6"><strong>Perfect for:</strong> Larger weddings (150+) who need beautiful indoor backup space without compromising on setting.</p>

